{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 22:28:04.979049", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and goal\\n- Topology: 2 leaves (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1), 2 spines (spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1), 1 super-spine (super_spine_router_0), hosts pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via leaf_router_0_0) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via leaf_router_0_1). EBGP on all interconnects (/31 on 172.16.0.0/16).\\n- Focus: detect anomalies, localize any faulty devices, and identify root cause.\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Overall network health is good. Host-to-host connectivity works with 0% loss and low latency. All EBGP sessions across leaves, spines, and super-spine are established and exchanging routes. Routing tables are consistent with the topology and support end-to-end reachability. No functional faults detected.\\n\\nKey observations and evidence\\n\\n1) Data-plane reachability\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 4/4 replies, 0% loss, avg ~2.4 ms, TTL 61 (indicates ~3 router hops, consistent with intra-pod path via leaf–spine–leaf).\\n- Wider reachability matrix (lab scope) shows 0% loss across tested pairs, with low, stable RTTs.\\n\\n2) Control-plane (BGP) status\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 EBGP neighbors up (AS 65100, 65101, 65102, 65103), State/PfxRcd=7 for each.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 EBGP neighbors up (AS 65100, 65101, 65102, 65103), State/PfxRcd=7 for each.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 6 EBGP neighbors up (two to AS 65000 and four leaves AS 65200–65203); receives 3–7 prefixes per neighbor, stable.\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 6 EBGP neighbors up (two to AS 65000 and four leaves AS 65200–65203); receives 5–6 prefixes per neighbor, stable.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 8 EBGP neighbors up (multiple spines), PfxRcd present from all.\\n- Up/Down timers ~00:00:38 across devices indicate recent bring-up, but sessions are stable and exchanging routes.\\n\\n3) Routing tables (selected)\\n- leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - C 10.0.0.0/24 (local host VLAN)\\n  - B 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.32 (one spine)\\n  - B 10.0.2.0/24 and 10.0.3.0/24 via 172.16.0.40 (the other spine)\\n  - B 10.1.x/24 via 172.16.0.32\\n- leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - C 10.0.1.0/24 (local host VLAN)\\n  - B 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.42\\n  - B 10.0.2.0/24 and 10.0.3.0/24 via 172.16.0.42\\n  - B 10.1.x/24 via 172.16.0.34\\n- spines and super-spine have consistent BGP-learned routes to all leaf /24s; spines show ECMP to some remote prefixes via the super-spine neighbors.\\n\\nDetected anomalies or irregularities\\n\\n- No functional reachability issues detected. All tested paths succeed with 0% loss and low latency.\\n- Observational notes (not faults):\\n  1) Leaf ECMP: Leaves appear to install a single best path per remote /24 (no ECMP entries), while spines show ECMP to some destinations. This is typical when eBGP maximum-paths/multipath is not configured on leaves; it is not a fault but a design/policy choice.\\n  2) Neighboring counts vs. provided subset: The BGP summaries show more neighbors than the small subset outlined in the prompt (e.g., leaves showing 4 spine peers and spines showing multiple super-spine peers). This likely reflects a larger lab fabric than the subset described, not a device fault.\\n  3) Prefix counts at spines per leaf vary slightly (e.g., 3–6 PfxRcd). Without an explicit expected baseline (how many leaf /24s exist and which are meant to be advertised where), this variability is not necessarily abnormal; it often occurs in larger topologies and with standard EBGP propagation.\\n\\nLocalization and root cause\\n\\n- Fault localization: No faulty device identified. All routers and links implicated in the pc_0_0 <-> pc_0_1 path are operating normally (both leafs, at least one spine, and the inter-leaf paths).\\n- Root cause: Not applicable. No outage, packet loss, or control-plane failure observed.\\n\\nConclusion\\n\\n- The data center Clos fabric is currently healthy for the examined hosts and routers. EBGP sessions are established and stable; forwarding tables are populated and consistent with the topology; end-to-end reachability is verified with normal latency and no loss.\\n- No actionable anomalies were detected at this time. Continuous monitoring is advised given the recent BGP session uptimes, but the present state indicates normal operation., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3092e13f-a0f4-46b1-b733-15dec17ab747'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
